Description: Tatsumi hopes to earn money for his village by working in the Capital, but that won’t be easy in a place where corruption is rampant and a league of assassins are the only good guys.
Title: AKAME GA KILL!, VOL. 1
Author: Takahiro and Tetsuya Tashiro

Description: Are werewolves and witches to blame for a series of gruesome deaths in Germany? Earl Ciel Phantomhive and his demon butler Sebastian investigate.
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 19
Author: Yana Toboso

Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: The origins of the Survey Corps leaders Levi and Erwin are told in this spinoff series.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: NO REGRETS, VOL. 2
Author: Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama
Contributor: by Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama

Description: Yuuki Asuna is yet another prisoner in the virtual reality game Sword Art Online. Can she apply her study habits as a top school student to her new, fantastical surroundings?
Title: SWORD ART ONLINE: PROGRESSIVE, VOL. 1
Author: Reki Kawahara and Kiseki Himura
Contributor: by Reki Kawahara and Kiseki Himura

Description: Sebastian is a loyal butler who moves easily from dinner parties to the underworld. Is he too good to be true? Is he even human?
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 1
Author: Yana Toboso

Description: In the not–too–distant future, a popular virtual reality video game traps its users, so the only way to log out is to beat the game. But if they die in the virtual world, it also means “game over” in the real world!
Title: SWORD ART ONLINE: AINCRAD
Author: Reki Kawahara and Tamako Nakamura
Contributor: by Reki Kawahara and Tamako Nakamura

Description: Yato is a god without a shrine. Or any worshipers for that matter. So, in order to build a lavish temple in his own honor, he takes on odd jobs and helps those in need for a nominal fee.
Title: NORAGAMI, VOL. 1
Author: Adachitoka

Description: The students of class of 3–E have only one assignment: kill the teacher! Of course, when that teacher is also a supremely powerful being, it is easier said than done.
Title: ASSASSINATION CLASSROOM, VOL. 1
Author: Yusei Matsui

Description: Follow the virtual (and musical) adventures of Hatsune Miku and her friends in this collected edition of stories, in black and white and color.
Title: UNOFFICIAL HATSUNE MIX
Author: KEI
